('The House on Paradise Street', 'Head of Zeus', 'Sofka Zinovieff', '9781781855869', 368, 'The House on Paradise Street is a novel set in Athens during the Second World War and the Greek Civil War. The novel follows the story of a young woman who becomes involved with the resistance movement and must navigate the dangerous political landscape of the time. The novel deals with themes of love, betrayal, and survival.', 'English', 'Historical fiction, War fiction, Resistance, Greece');

